This is due to the fact that when an autocomplete operation is cancelled it leaves behind this markup in the editor: 

{code}
<td> ... <textnode: "{info"> I </td>
{code}

Where "{{I}}" is the cursor, notice how autocomplete leaves behind a text node which contains the value "{info" and leaves the cursor _after_ this text node. 

We already have logic in autoformat that _moves_ the a cursor in this particular position into the text node just proceeding it. At the moment it only applies to headers and paragraphs. We should generalise the logic to apply not to particular blocks but to when the cursor is after a text node (allowing it to apply here as well). 

This is only apparent now because we are autoformatting macros. Autoformatting bold does not exhibit this issue as it doesn't position the cursor after a text node.

